  "accessibility": {
    "standard": "WCAG 2.1 (body 4.5:1, large/UI 3:1) plus a Machado-2009 CVD pass at full severity.",
    "lit": {
      "whale on pitch": 15.79,
      "gull on pitch": 6.82,
      "fire on pitch": 4.64,
      "iron on fire": 4.68,
      "foam on pitch": 8.3
    },
    "cold": {
      "ink on paper": 12.21,
      "muted on paper": 4.91,
      "fire on paper": 4.61,
      "button on fire": 5.05,
      "sea-bright on paper": 4.67
    },
    "cvd": "Identity hues (sea vs fire) separate cleanly under protan/deutan/tritan. In the code tier the blue/amber axis is CVD-safe; residual close pairs (blue function vs violet number under deutan; blue vs cyan under tritan; amber vs red under tritan) sit on rarely-adjacent tokens and are reinforced with weight and italics (bold keywords, italic types and comments). Run scripts/cvd_check.py for the full table.",
    "rules": [
      "Amber fills on the sea use flame with dark iron text (ember on sea is below 3:1).",
      "Fire-rare is an identity-tier rule; the code tier follows accessibility-first syntax logic with fire on keywords.",
      "Borders are deliberately faint; lift only if visible separators are wanted."
    ]
  },
  "notes": "0.5.0 re-founds the system on a closer reading of chapter 96: the steady light is the guide, the fire is the rare and dangerous mark. Scarcity becomes an ethic, not a layout rule; the code exception is named; conviviality and provisionality are stated in FOUNDATIONS.md. Colours and surfaces unchanged from 0.4.0.",
